The White House Press Secretary released a statement expressing condolences for the death of Oswaldo Payá, a prominent activist in Cuba known for his advocacy for civic and human rights. Payá dedicated his life to nonviolent efforts for freedom and democratic reform in Cuba through organizations like the Christian Liberation Movement and the Varela Project. The statement recognizes Payá's optimism and commitment to a peaceful transition in Cuba and states that the United States will continue to support the Cuban people in their pursuit of human rights.